WEBVTT

1
00:00:41.096 --> 00:00:43.567
I'll give you information about
my missions. about my tradecraft.

2
00:00:43.568 --> 00:00:45.904
but nothing about the people I work with...

3
00:00:47.988 --> 00:00:49.438
I won't endanger anyone.

4
00:00:49.439 --> 00:00:51.240
Then why are you defecting?

5
00:00:52.772 --> 00:00:53.890
For that?

6
00:00:54.090 --> 00:00:56.890
_

7
00:00:56.891 --> 00:01:00.226
_

8
00:01:00.492 --> 00:01:02.767
- _
- _

9
00:01:03.265 --> 00:01:06.501
You and the traitor will
be debriefed separately.

10
00:01:16.384 --> 00:01:18.977
It's a trap. Run.

11
00:01:37.947 --> 00:01:40.838
---

12
00:02:35.897 --> 00:02:37.286
I need to go.

13
00:03:33.135 --> 00:03:37.353
Report from Katia M. secretary to
Oleg Dornin. Soviet trade envoy.

14
00:03:37.628 --> 00:03:39.247
Questioned in character for 11 hours

15
00:03:39.248 --> 00:03:41.865
but did not retrieve any notable intel.

16
00:03:41.866 --> 00:03:44.040
Instead have obtained
pictures of appointments diary

17
00:03:44.041 --> 00:03:46.664
covering January and February 1972.

18
00:03:46.665 --> 00:03:49.329
Also enclosed are copies
of family photographs.

19
00:03:49.330 --> 00:03:50.841
Registry currently cross-referencing

20
00:03:50.842 --> 00:03:53.672
in case any subjects
are persons of interest.

21
00:03:55.638 --> 00:03:57.179
Report ends.

22
00:04:20.564 --> 00:04:25.987
Synced and corrected by chamallow
www.addic7ed.com

23
00:05:03.543 --> 00:05:07.454
And. let me tell you.
I worshipped that man.

24
00:05:07.455 --> 00:05:09.996
But confidence is on the floor.

25
00:05:09.997 --> 00:05:13.414
And in our game. insecurity can cost lives.

26
00:05:13.415 --> 00:05:16.060
Now. my chief concern... My only concern.

27
00:05:16.061 --> 00:05:18.614
is what's best for the
department. the country.

28
00:05:18.779 --> 00:05:21.473
the memory of that once great man.

29
00:05:21.474 --> 00:05:22.464
Now...

30
00:05:22.465 --> 00:05:24.736
- Call for you. Mr Waterhouse.
- Wait!

31
00:05:26.387 --> 00:05:29.648
Now. some have suggested
that I take the reins. I...

32
00:05:30.263 --> 00:05:32.941
All I can say is. the thought's
never occurred to me...

33
00:05:32.941 --> 00:05:34.658
It's not my mother. is it?

34
00:05:35.745 --> 00:05:38.142
{a9}

35
00:05:38.143 --> 00:05:41.931
<i>The strategic arms limitation
talks continue in Helsinki.</i>

36
00:05:42.253 --> 00:05:45.451
<i>However. proceedings were delayed
today when the U.S. delegation</i>

37
00:05:45.452 --> 00:05:47.709
refused to attend the morning session

38
00:05:47.710 --> 00:05:50.185
after hearing reports that the U.S.S.R.

39
00:05:50.186 --> 00:05:53.462
had. in fact. stepped up production
of anti-ballistic missiles

40
00:05:53.463 --> 00:05:55.350
instead of freezing it.

41
00:05:55.785 --> 00:06:00.001
Domestic news. As the miners'
strike enters its fifth week.

42
00:06:00.002 --> 00:06:03.990
power cuts and other restrictions are
being introduced across the country.

43
00:06:03.991 --> 00:06:04.177
{a9}---

44
00:06:04.178 --> 00:06:07.830
Here's a report from our
correspondent. Martin Bell.

45
00:06:08.345 --> 00:06:10.540
The first effect of the
emergency will be seen

46
00:06:10.541 --> 00:06:12.641
in the darkening of city centres.

47
00:06:12.642 --> 00:06:14.650
In fact. it's already started...

48
00:06:14.651 --> 00:06:16.478
Sarah. do you need this one?

49
00:06:17.004 --> 00:06:18.251
All yours.

50
00:06:18.252 --> 00:06:19.277
With me.

51
00:06:19.278 --> 00:06:23.001
... for from then it becomes
an offence to use electricity

52
00:06:23.002 --> 00:06:24.935
for advertising or floodlighting.

53
00:06:24.936 --> 00:06:26.575
The penalty for such an offence...

54
00:06:26.576 --> 00:06:29.849
... a £100 pound fine. or
three months in jail. or both.

55
00:06:29.850 --> 00:06:31.857
The emergency regulations will also relieve

56
00:06:31.858 --> 00:06:34.516
the electricity authorities
of their responsibility

57
00:06:34.517 --> 00:06:36.625
to maintain uninterrupted supplies.

58
00:06:36.626 --> 00:06:38.034
So. they'll be able to economise

59
00:06:38.035 --> 00:06:42.004
where they have to. and to keep
the power flowing where it's needed.

60
00:06:57.092 --> 00:06:58.824
What was she talking to you about?

61
00:06:58.825 --> 00:07:00.727
- What?
- Her.

62
00:07:01.281 --> 00:07:03.608
Sarah. Daddy's girl. What was she saying?

63
00:07:03.609 --> 00:07:04.891
Nothing.

64
00:07:05.054 --> 00:07:07.092
She was watching the news.

65
00:07:07.380 --> 00:07:09.214
I went in to watch it with her.

66
00:07:18.884 --> 00:07:20.696
Thick as thieves. you two.

67
00:07:23.391 --> 00:07:27.027
So. Arkady Malinov.

68
00:07:29.183 --> 00:07:31.256
Since '62. he's been a lecturer

69
00:07:31.257 --> 00:07:33.123
at Reading University. for his sins.

70
00:07:33.124 --> 00:07:35.573
Pure as the driven. so
we thought. until today.

71
00:07:35.574 --> 00:07:38.041
when he drinks a bath full of vodka

72
00:07:38.042 --> 00:07:40.089
and punches a policeman.

73
00:07:42.733 --> 00:07:47.638
But once in custody. he lets it be
known that he is in fact. Colonel

74
00:07:47.639 --> 00:07:52.130
Arkady blah-blah of the Committee for
State Security and wishes to parley.

75
00:07:52.607 --> 00:07:56.964
So. we've released him. told him to roll up at
the Olympic Hotel in Earls Court later today.

76
00:07:56.965 --> 00:08:00.646
There he shall have the dubious
pleasure of being debriefed by you.

77
00:08:00.647 --> 00:08:02.810
- Why me?
- Oh. Don't look at me.

78
00:08:02.811 --> 00:08:04.744
It was Daddy's idea.

79
00:08:05.121 --> 00:08:09.798
After that fiasco in Poland. I was
lobbying for you to get your P45.

80
00:08:10.035 --> 00:08:11.843
That's what they call it. isn't it?

81
00:08:12.342 --> 00:08:16.445
We had to give up three of our
most prized catches to get you back.

82
00:08:18.695 --> 00:08:21.240
I mean. what were you even doing there?

83
00:08:27.210 --> 00:08:29.673
I'll give you information about
my missions. about my tradecraft.

84
00:08:29.674 --> 00:08:31.961
but nothing about the people I work with...

85
00:08:33.451 --> 00:08:35.152
I won't endanger anyone.

86
00:08:42.566 --> 00:08:45.181
I was following up on a possible defection.

87
00:08:47.758 --> 00:08:50.826
Well. we are a merciful bunch. apparently.

88
00:08:50.827 --> 00:08:53.282
Hence. this chance to redeem yourself.

89
00:08:53.283 --> 00:08:55.553
Look. chances are. he just wants to defect.

90
00:08:55.554 --> 00:08:58.657
So. convince him to stay on the
Kremlin's payroll and work for us.

91
00:08:58.658 --> 00:09:01.217
Take Alan with you. he'll be your ears.

92
00:09:01.218 --> 00:09:02.529
Chin up!

93
00:09:02.530 --> 00:09:06.279
It'll make a nice change from bedding
secretaries and forgotten wives. no?

94
00:09:18.189 --> 00:09:20.465
So. Joe.

95
00:09:20.565 --> 00:09:23.606
How do you like to spend your free time?

96
00:09:23.806 --> 00:09:26.163
Are you a member of a team or club?

97
00:09:26.164 --> 00:09:28.413
Maybe you enjoy more solitary pursuits...

98
00:09:28.960 --> 00:09:31.900
Ah. like model-making or canoeing?

99
00:09:35.970 --> 00:09:39.603
Yeah. as you know. small
talk isn't my strong suit.

100
00:09:39.604 --> 00:09:44.488
So. actually. Sarah thought that a
list of prepared topics might help.

101
00:09:44.792 --> 00:09:46.898
Um. "Mutual friends."

102
00:09:47.069 --> 00:09:48.234
Bit sticky.

103
00:09:48.235 --> 00:09:50.701
"Politics." Bit of a minefield.

104
00:09:50.702 --> 00:09:53.021
"Sport." Gosh. no.

105
00:09:53.466 --> 00:09:56.610
"Leisure activities." That's all I have.

106
00:09:56.611 --> 00:09:57.905
It's fine.

107
00:09:58.842 --> 00:10:00.531
We'll talk about work.

108
00:10:01.791 --> 00:10:02.899
Thank you.

109
00:10:03.371 --> 00:10:06.799
Right! That's one in the lamp. one
in the showerhead in the bathroom.

110
00:10:06.922 --> 00:10:08.626
I need to check the levels.

111
00:10:08.627 --> 00:10:11.135
When I tap on the wall. you say something.

112
00:10:11.182 --> 00:10:12.489
Like what?

113
00:10:12.490 --> 00:10:15.476
- Oh. anything. A nursery rhyme.
- I don't know any.

114
00:10:16.721 --> 00:10:18.664
Everyone knows a nursery rhyme.

115
00:10:18.951 --> 00:10:20.605
Frère Jacques?

116
00:10:21.786 --> 00:10:23.424
Pease Pudding Hot?

117
00:10:24.797 --> 00:10:26.642
Yesterday Upon the Stair.

118
00:10:27.126 --> 00:10:29.618
- I know that one.
- Capital.

119
00:10:33.019 --> 00:10:34.906
Yesterday. upon the stair.

120
00:10:37.454 --> 00:10:39.687
I met a man who wasn't there.

121
00:11:09.093 --> 00:11:10.282
He's here.

122
00:11:25.926 --> 00:11:27.960
- How long have we got?
- An hour.

123
00:11:34.917 --> 00:11:36.445
You understand we cannot discuss payments

124
00:11:36.446 --> 00:11:38.244
until your debrief has been completed.

125
00:11:38.245 --> 00:11:39.933
This takes about six months

126
00:11:39.934 --> 00:11:42.712
and your product assessed.

127
00:11:43.436 --> 00:11:44.601
Colonel?

128
00:11:45.940 --> 00:11:47.254
Yeah.

129
00:11:50.545 --> 00:11:53.371
Though. of course. our
rates of pay increase.

130
00:11:53.372 --> 00:11:57.193
if you stay in situ and help us
gather intel on a more regular basis.

131
00:11:57.223 --> 00:11:59.416
Yes. this is what I want.

132
00:11:59.604 --> 00:12:01.833
I am going to work for MI5.

133
00:12:01.834 --> 00:12:03.839
Well. that's very nice of you.

134
00:12:05.035 --> 00:12:06.884
So. you know the drill.

135
00:12:06.900 --> 00:12:09.588
We'll start with your name and rank.
then move onto your war record.

136
00:12:09.589 --> 00:12:11.030
There is no time.

137
00:12:11.875 --> 00:12:15.079
I have information about
a major KGB operation

138
00:12:15.080 --> 00:12:18.400
about to take place on United Kingdom soil.

139
00:12:19.348 --> 00:12:21.720
It has been named Operation Glass.

140
00:12:25.302 --> 00:12:27.812
What are the objectives of this operation?

141
00:12:28.488 --> 00:12:29.878
I don't know.

142
00:12:30.141 --> 00:12:32.209
Well. how many people does it involve?

143
00:12:32.880 --> 00:12:34.192
I don't know.

144
00:12:34.268 --> 00:12:36.384
Why is it called Operation Glass?

145
00:12:36.648 --> 00:12:39.307
- I do not know.
- So exactly which bit of this plan

146
00:12:39.308 --> 00:12:42.086
that you know nothing about
has offended you so much

147
00:12:42.087 --> 00:12:44.214
that you want to betray your country?

148
00:12:55.302 --> 00:12:58.686
Years from now. the story of
British and Soviet espionage

149
00:12:58.687 --> 00:13:02.557
will be divided into before
and after this moment.

150
00:13:02.775 --> 00:13:06.137
Before and after Operation Glass.

151
00:13:06.379 --> 00:13:09.096
They are going to tear everything down.

152
00:13:09.173 --> 00:13:11.408
At this point. I paused the interview.

153
00:13:12.023 --> 00:13:13.802
I needed to speak to Bobby.

154
00:13:14.133 --> 00:13:17.954
I asked Alan to babysit Arkady. I
went downstairs to phone The Fray.

155
00:13:21.497 --> 00:13:25.656
For product of this quality.
Arkady wanted £10.000

156
00:13:25.657 --> 00:13:26.819
and a new identity.

157
00:13:26.820 --> 00:13:31.282
I said not a penny more then 5.000 and
a new identity would only be provided

158
00:13:31.283 --> 00:13:35.131
if the veracity of this operation were proven.

159
00:13:35.132 --> 00:13:38.190
He grumbled a bit but
seemed generally satisfied

160
00:13:38.660 --> 00:13:41.611
and told me everything he
knows about Operation Glass.

161
00:13:42.656 --> 00:13:44.231
I have a name.

162
00:13:45.014 --> 00:13:47.934
As time goes on. I will have more.

163
00:13:50.117 --> 00:13:55.139
Each a retired or inactive
agent. a British citizen.

164
00:13:55.368 --> 00:13:57.912
Each name come with an instruction

165
00:13:57.944 --> 00:13:59.503
just for them.

166
00:13:59.504 --> 00:14:02.502
I will approach them
and give them their task.

167
00:14:02.642 --> 00:14:04.482
How are you given the names?

168
00:14:08.228 --> 00:14:09.971
A dead-letter drop.

169
00:14:10.092 --> 00:14:13.483
The men's' toilets in Boston Manor Park.

170
00:14:13.484 --> 00:14:15.458
I know to pick it up
because they put advert

171
00:14:15.459 --> 00:14:17.849
in classified ads in The Times.

172
00:14:17.850 --> 00:14:21.361
It say. "Cousin Andrew. Please visit us."

173
00:14:21.535 --> 00:14:23.174
Who's the first agent?

174
00:14:23.605 --> 00:14:25.165
David Hexton.

175
00:14:25.775 --> 00:14:28.908
He used to work in. er.
Ministry of Agriculture.

176
00:14:28.909 --> 00:14:31.284
You still haven't told
me why you're turning.

177
00:14:38.991 --> 00:14:40.385
Why am I turning?

178
00:14:43.135 --> 00:14:45.009
I want to be a capitalist.

179
00:14:46.840 --> 00:14:49.102
I want to read The Times

180
00:14:49.219 --> 00:14:52.782
and see the Oxford and Cambridge boat race.

181
00:14:52.783 --> 00:14:54.426
I want my children to go to Eton.

182
00:14:54.427 --> 00:14:57.272
You should know more about this plan.

183
00:14:59.551 --> 00:15:01.307
What aren't you telling me?

184
00:15:06.315 --> 00:15:07.688
Understand this.

185
00:15:08.445 --> 00:15:10.613
Operation Glass is a jigsaw.

186
00:15:10.794 --> 00:15:13.072
No one sees all the pieces.

187
00:15:13.646 --> 00:15:16.813
But all the world will
see the finished picture.

188
00:15:16.814 --> 00:15:21.937
"A jigsaw." I mean... "Planned in the
shadows." What is he talking about?

189
00:15:21.938 --> 00:15:23.743
I hate it when they try to be enigmatic.

190
00:15:23.744 --> 00:15:27.211
Well. in terms of "why". this
new desire for a Western life.

191
00:15:27.212 --> 00:15:29.688
something about it doesn't sit quite right.

192
00:15:29.844 --> 00:15:33.299
But as for. "Why now". it's as I said.

193
00:15:33.300 --> 00:15:37.281
years of being ignored. denied
significant operational responsibility.

194
00:15:37.282 --> 00:15:38.811
he's lost loyalty to the cause.

195
00:15:38.812 --> 00:15:42.311
Yes. but this Operation Glass.
if it succeeds. if it's real.

196
00:15:42.312 --> 00:15:43.949
won't that reflect well on him?

197
00:15:43.950 --> 00:15:45.875
I see what Joe's getting at.

198
00:15:45.876 --> 00:15:49.133
Arkady is only a postman and he knows it.

199
00:15:49.320 --> 00:15:51.359
He's finally been invited to the top table

200
00:15:51.360 --> 00:15:53.339
and he's just dishing out the soup.

201
00:15:53.340 --> 00:15:56.632
If he wrecks the whole
thing. he's in control.

202
00:15:56.633 --> 00:15:59.611
He's important. perhaps. for
the first time in his career.

203
00:15:59.612 --> 00:16:02.890
It all sounds damn fishy to me. I mean.

204
00:16:02.891 --> 00:16:04.989
he's broken enough legs
to make colonel in the KGB.

205
00:16:04.990 --> 00:16:09.306
but he's going to turn his back on the whole
lot because he fancies a trip to Harrods?

206
00:16:09.307 --> 00:16:11.209
Daddy. some sense. I implore you.

207
00:16:11.210 --> 00:16:14.494
We are ancient nations. we
both want this war to end.

208
00:16:14.495 --> 00:16:17.972
Eventually. one of us would find
a way to break the stalemate.

209
00:16:18.787 --> 00:16:21.973
But the warrior who lifts
his arm for the killer blow

210
00:16:23.068 --> 00:16:25.377
leaves his heart exposed.

211
00:16:28.425 --> 00:16:30.143
Bloody miners!

212
00:16:48.066 --> 00:16:49.350
Working?

213
00:16:49.688 --> 00:16:51.351
On a Sunday?

214
00:16:56.147 --> 00:16:58.038
No. Er...

215
00:16:58.567 --> 00:17:01.517
Yes. um. bit of a breakthrough at work.

216
00:17:01.518 --> 00:17:03.402
Netted a big fish.

217
00:17:03.403 --> 00:17:06.683
It's all very hush-hush. but.
er. all hands to the pump.

218
00:17:06.927 --> 00:17:09.852
Do they appreciate you. my darling?

219
00:17:10.565 --> 00:17:13.048
- Shall I talk to them again?
- No!

220
00:17:13.049 --> 00:17:15.081
God. no.

221
00:17:15.105 --> 00:17:16.716
No. they're cock-a-hoop with me.

222
00:17:16.717 --> 00:17:18.050
Really. Full of praise.

223
00:17:18.051 --> 00:17:19.988
No. this. um...

224
00:17:21.918 --> 00:17:24.416
Daddy's formed a special committee.

225
00:17:25.147 --> 00:17:26.863
Asked for me personally.

226
00:17:38.136 --> 00:17:40.944
My Hercules.

227
00:17:41.034 --> 00:17:44.703
You'll bring glory to our name once more.

228
00:17:45.654 --> 00:17:47.182
Won't you?

229
00:17:47.873 --> 00:17:49.181
Mother. really.

230
00:17:49.510 --> 00:17:51.050
you are too much!

231
00:17:51.051 --> 00:17:52.785
Now. I will not stand for this!

232
00:17:52.786 --> 00:17:56.214
You'll do as you're
bloody well told. darling.

233
00:18:21.163 --> 00:18:23.836
Moscow will give the names
of the agents to Arkady

234
00:18:23.837 --> 00:18:26.776
one by one via a dead-letter drop.

235
00:18:26.793 --> 00:18:29.647
The first is David Hexton. By now.

236
00:18:29.648 --> 00:18:33.449
Arkady will have activated him
and passed on instructions.

237
00:18:33.450 --> 00:18:36.255
You debriefed Arkady. you're
inclined to believe him.

238
00:18:36.256 --> 00:18:38.745
The only time that I thought
Arkady was actually lying to me

239
00:18:38.746 --> 00:18:41.018
was when I asked him why he was turning.

240
00:18:41.019 --> 00:18:43.336
He moved the ashtray
and placed it between us.

241
00:18:43.337 --> 00:18:48.029
Liars often place objects between
themselves and the person they're talking to.

242
00:18:48.030 --> 00:18:52.404
I want to read The Times and see
the Oxford and Cambridge boat race.

243
00:18:52.405 --> 00:18:54.759
But you believe the operation is real?

244
00:18:54.760 --> 00:18:59.079
And regardless of his motivations. you
believe Arkady is genuinely switching sides?

245
00:18:59.080 --> 00:19:01.373
- Yes.
- I'm sorry. I don't mean to. er...

246
00:19:01.374 --> 00:19:03.695
I'm. I'm right in saying that

247
00:19:03.696 --> 00:19:09.751
you don't know actually what
Operation Glass is. do you?

248
00:19:12.415 --> 00:19:14.471
Can I just ask who this chap is?

249
00:19:14.472 --> 00:19:16.387
Sorry. it's just we
haven't been introduced.

250
00:19:16.388 --> 00:19:20.452
Unless I missed it? Did you all introduce
yourselves while I was padlocking my bike?

251
00:19:20.555 --> 00:19:23.646
This is Detective Constable Jim
Fenchurch from Special Branch.

252
00:19:23.647 --> 00:19:26.617
Jim will be joining us
as our police liaison.

253
00:19:26.618 --> 00:19:28.734
Jim. this is Bobby Waterhouse.

254
00:19:28.735 --> 00:19:31.685
head of Counter-Espionage
here at The Fray.

255
00:19:31.942 --> 00:19:36.062
Sarah Montag. his deputy. but also
what we like to call a reflector.

256
00:19:36.063 --> 00:19:40.287
She has a genius for deducing
motives and intentions.

257
00:19:40.288 --> 00:19:42.819
You said The Fray.

258
00:19:43.145 --> 00:19:46.039
- Well. what's The Fray?
- Where we find ourselves now.

259
00:19:46.345 --> 00:19:48.872
The central offices of MI5.

260
00:19:49.920 --> 00:19:51.931
Alan. her husband.

261
00:19:51.932 --> 00:19:56.178
one of our nosey parkers. in
charge of bugs and wire-taps

262
00:19:56.274 --> 00:19:57.426
and

263
00:19:57.427 --> 00:19:58.660
Joe Lambe.

264
00:19:58.661 --> 00:20:03.452
A man of. er. obscure
and formidable talents.

265
00:20:04.354 --> 00:20:07.237
And of course. Wendy.

266
00:20:07.238 --> 00:20:09.458
on loan from the Nannies.

267
00:20:09.459 --> 00:20:12.498
So. Jim. You were saying.

268
00:20:12.778 --> 00:20:15.151
Yeah. you don't actually

269
00:20:15.181 --> 00:20:17.203
know what it is you're investigating.

270
00:20:17.204 --> 00:20:19.909
This isn't a conventional war. Jim.

271
00:20:20.255 --> 00:20:25.138
The objectives. even our own.
are unclear and ever-changing.

272
00:20:25.139 --> 00:20:26.774
Do the Soviets want to oppress us?

273
00:20:26.775 --> 00:20:29.034
Without question. But how?

274
00:20:29.035 --> 00:20:30.298
Will they invade us?

275
00:20:30.299 --> 00:20:33.436
Will they raise us to the
ground with a nuclear strike?

276
00:20:33.533 --> 00:20:36.718
Or will they infiltrate and
destabilise us from the inside?

277
00:20:36.719 --> 00:20:38.522
We don't know.

278
00:20:38.679 --> 00:20:43.189
It is a war of variables and unknowns
and all we can do is watch.

279
00:20:43.452 --> 00:20:45.918
surmise. and react.

280
00:20:47.537 --> 00:20:50.485
Bobby. talk to everyone in
your legendary address book.

281
00:20:50.486 --> 00:20:52.247
Alan. I want you to go through every inch

282
00:20:52.248 --> 00:20:56.209
of recorded conversation.
flagging the word "Glass."

283
00:20:56.210 --> 00:20:59.309
Joe. take Jim. contact David.

284
00:20:59.617 --> 00:21:01.451
find out what his instructions are

285
00:21:01.452 --> 00:21:03.827
and attempt to get him into bed with us.

286
00:21:03.828 --> 00:21:05.148
Wendy.

287
00:21:21.585 --> 00:21:24.828
Joe. A quick word. Um. I'm...

288
00:21:26.187 --> 00:21:27.993
... worried about Daddy.

289
00:21:28.477 --> 00:21:31.259
We all know his tenure has
been. shall we say. lacklustre.

290
00:21:31.260 --> 00:21:32.797
One more cock-up. he'll
be getting his clock.

291
00:21:32.798 --> 00:21:35.637
which will be heart-breaking.
blah-blah. but may be a blessing.

292
00:21:35.638 --> 00:21:37.978
Put the old dog out of his misery. I mean.

293
00:21:38.650 --> 00:21:41.304
the business with the Chinese dancer.

294
00:21:41.815 --> 00:21:43.970
People gossip. it's ghastly.
but that's people for you.

295
00:21:43.971 --> 00:21:45.661
Now what to do?

296
00:21:48.709 --> 00:21:50.823
Perhaps you could keep an eye on him.

297
00:21:51.190 --> 00:21:54.082
Talk to him. see what's going
on in that once-great noggin.

298
00:21:54.573 --> 00:21:55.870
And report back to you.

299
00:21:55.871 --> 00:21:58.568
Someone has to mind the shop.
The old man is losing his grip.

300
00:21:58.569 --> 00:22:00.180
I'm not the right man for this.

301
00:22:00.181 --> 00:22:03.173
- But Daddy trusts you.
- Which is why I'm not the...

302
00:22:05.183 --> 00:22:05.982
Forget it.

303
00:22:05.983 --> 00:22:08.149
This is no time for sentiment. Joe.

304
00:22:08.482 --> 00:22:10.304
We must look to the future.

305
00:22:10.722 --> 00:22:12.537
It's just a game. Bobby.

306
00:22:12.919 --> 00:22:14.498
And this is why.

307
00:22:37.770 --> 00:22:39.584
I didn't ask for this assignment.

308
00:22:39.860 --> 00:22:41.466
I want to make that clear.

309
00:22:42.063 --> 00:22:43.493
I don't agree with you.

310
00:22:44.867 --> 00:22:47.733
- You don't agree with us?
- Why is he called Daddy?

311
00:22:48.601 --> 00:22:50.661
It's childish. What's his real name?

312
00:22:51.074 --> 00:22:53.101
No one knows.

313
00:22:53.787 --> 00:22:55.946
What do you mean you don't agree with us?

314
00:22:57.374 --> 00:22:59.387
I'm not impressed by this world.

315
00:23:00.328 --> 00:23:01.542
You're arrogant.

316
00:23:02.049 --> 00:23:03.975
Not you.

317
00:23:04.566 --> 00:23:06.015
- "You."
- Yeah.

318
00:23:06.016 --> 00:23:07.478
You think you're above the law.

319
00:23:07.479 --> 00:23:09.310
I think this is a
conversation for another time.

320
00:23:09.311 --> 00:23:11.611
- I'm not impressed.
- Yeah. yeah.

321
00:23:13.110 --> 00:23:14.919
You might have mentioned that.

322
00:23:17.168 --> 00:23:19.377
Right. I need you to get us in there.

323
00:23:19.378 --> 00:23:22.917
I don't have any jurisdiction.
After that. just stand there.

324
00:23:22.918 --> 00:23:25.478
Be stoic. What you've been doing.

325
00:23:25.729 --> 00:23:27.380
Be unimpressed.

326
00:23:28.172 --> 00:23:31.494
- And my name's Henderson.
- I thought it was Lambe.

327
00:23:31.495 --> 00:23:34.247
It is. It just isn't here.

328
00:23:38.912 --> 00:23:40.270
David Hexton?

329
00:23:40.333 --> 00:23:43.044
I'm Detective Constable
James Fenchurch. This is

330
00:23:43.458 --> 00:23:46.201
Mr Henderson. We'd like to talk to you.

331
00:23:46.854 --> 00:23:48.348
Oh. thank God.

332
00:23:49.428 --> 00:23:50.663
Thank God.

333
00:24:00.864 --> 00:24:02.677
I want to make it absolutely...

334
00:24:03.045 --> 00:24:06.085
I've had no contact. no dealings with. uh.

335
00:24:06.086 --> 00:24:07.284
with Russia for years.

336
00:24:07.285 --> 00:24:10.067
Until yesterday. when one of
their agents approached you.

337
00:24:10.068 --> 00:24:11.783
Yes. yes. that's...

338
00:24:12.360 --> 00:24:14.303
- That's right.
- What did he give you?

339
00:24:26.507 --> 00:24:29.015
It's encrypted in the same
code I used when I was...

340
00:24:29.905 --> 00:24:31.373
When I worked for them.

341
00:24:31.374 --> 00:24:32.838
What does it say?

342
00:24:33.710 --> 00:24:36.331
An address. a flat in Marylebone.

343
00:24:36.332 --> 00:24:38.960
Underneath it is the
name of a letting agent.

344
00:24:39.108 --> 00:24:42.759
The instruction is to go to
them and to lease that flat.

345
00:24:43.662 --> 00:24:44.828
And?

346
00:24:44.829 --> 00:24:46.432
- That's it.
- That's it?

347
00:24:46.892 --> 00:24:48.551
- Lease a flat?
- Yeah.

348
00:24:48.552 --> 00:24:50.234
So you've done that already?

349
00:24:50.486 --> 00:24:52.557
Yesterday. Straight away.

350
00:24:59.105 --> 00:25:00.971
What are you supposed to do with these now

351
00:25:00.972 --> 00:25:03.098
for the man who approached you yesterday?
Are you meant to give them to him?

352
00:25:03.099 --> 00:25:05.743
No. he. uh. said he was just a messenger.

353
00:25:05.746 --> 00:25:07.784
Someone was coming to pick them up today.

354
00:25:08.545 --> 00:25:10.143
I thought you were them.

355
00:25:10.192 --> 00:25:13.260
Right. when they come.
this is what you say.

356
00:25:13.261 --> 00:25:16.040
You tell them that the estate agent
still hasn't given you the keys.

357
00:25:16.041 --> 00:25:17.535
you're picking them up this evening.

358
00:25:17.536 --> 00:25:19.556
We need to get into that flat first.

359
00:25:19.557 --> 00:25:21.883
Tell them to meet you
there tonight at 9:00 p.m..

360
00:25:21.884 --> 00:25:24.189
no earlier. to hand over
the keys. have you got that?

361
00:25:24.190 --> 00:25:25.847
But you'll be there instead.

362
00:25:25.848 --> 00:25:27.230
No. we'll be there as well.

363
00:25:27.231 --> 00:25:29.015
You'll give them the keys.

364
00:25:29.051 --> 00:25:30.851
you'll act as if nothing's wrong.

365
00:25:32.317 --> 00:25:33.556
I thought you'd

366
00:25:33.557 --> 00:25:35.175
- come to help me...
- By the way. Operation Glass.

367
00:25:35.176 --> 00:25:37.064
does that mean anything to you?

368
00:25:37.343 --> 00:25:38.098
Er... No...

369
00:25:38.099 --> 00:25:40.391
Or perhaps someone mentioned it when
you were working with the Soviets?

370
00:25:40.392 --> 00:25:42.432
Never. Look. about tonight. I really...

371
00:25:42.433 --> 00:25:43.954
Why did you do it?

372
00:25:46.597 --> 00:25:49.122
Betray your country. Hmm?

373
00:25:49.744 --> 00:25:50.864
I'm curious.

374
00:25:50.865 --> 00:25:54.631
Look. I only worked for the Ministry of
Agriculture. I couldn't give them anything.

375
00:25:55.116 --> 00:25:57.013
I don't know. crucial.

376
00:26:01.978 --> 00:26:03.417
It's my wife.

377
00:26:05.427 --> 00:26:06.846
She's East German.

378
00:26:07.325 --> 00:26:10.388
The Soviets allowed her to emigrate
in exchange for information.

379
00:26:10.389 --> 00:26:11.989
I did it for her.

380
00:26:13.159 --> 00:26:15.032
I did it to be with her.

381
00:26:18.086 --> 00:26:20.046
9:00 p.m. Don't forget.

382
00:26:35.199 --> 00:26:36.866
- Who is it?
- Them.

383
00:26:36.884 --> 00:26:38.354
The KGB?

384
00:26:47.841 --> 00:26:49.073
They're here.

385
00:26:55.012 --> 00:26:56.282
You are joking?

386
00:26:56.775 --> 00:26:58.553
Welcome to MI5.

387
00:27:11.488 --> 00:27:12.702
Hello. David.

388
00:27:12.846 --> 00:27:14.856
- You are alone?
- Yes.

389
00:27:17.821 --> 00:27:20.376
- It is done?
- Yes. yes.

390
00:27:24.184 --> 00:27:29.209
But the. uh. the thing is. the letting
agent hasn't given me the keys yet.

391
00:27:29.245 --> 00:27:31.421
I'm. uh. picking them up this evening.

392
00:27:37.866 --> 00:27:40.316
So I thought I could meet
you there and hand them over.

393
00:27:40.317 --> 00:27:41.766
About 9:00?

394
00:27:42.143 --> 00:27:43.982
You're not lying to me. are you?

395
00:27:45.075 --> 00:27:46.414
Of course not.

396
00:27:49.332 --> 00:27:50.735
Is there anything else?

397
00:27:51.522 --> 00:27:54.951
It's just. my wife's due
back from work any minute.

398
00:27:56.031 --> 00:27:57.701
No. no. no. no.

399
00:27:59.596 --> 00:28:00.847
See you later.

400
00:28:15.059 --> 00:28:16.276
That's it.

401
00:28:16.929 --> 00:28:18.578
I'm sorry. I can't do this. I can't.

402
00:28:18.579 --> 00:28:20.140
can't go through with it.

403
00:28:20.673 --> 00:28:23.810
I'd fall apart. I know it.
I'd. uh. say the wrong thing.

404
00:28:35.304 --> 00:28:39.308
No! No! Get off me!

405
00:28:39.576 --> 00:28:41.546
Couldn't someone pose as the
letting agent. say. or even...

406
00:28:41.547 --> 00:28:42.932
Shut up.

407
00:28:43.069 --> 00:28:45.201
You passed information
to a hostile government.

408
00:28:45.202 --> 00:28:46.655
Harmless info...

409
00:28:46.656 --> 00:28:49.184
Crop yields. the efficiency
of certain fertilisers...

410
00:28:49.185 --> 00:28:51.507
A regime that might be about to
put our entire country under siege.

411
00:28:51.508 --> 00:28:53.476
You told them how much food we have.

412
00:28:53.477 --> 00:28:55.716
You told them how to
make chemical weaponry!

413
00:28:56.499 --> 00:28:57.629
Now you're going to do this.

414
00:28:57.630 --> 00:28:59.820
You are going to serve the country
you betrayed or I'll make sure

415
00:28:59.821 --> 00:29:02.938
your wife gets deported and you
spend the rest of your life in prison.

416
00:29:02.939 --> 00:29:04.422
Is that clear?

417
00:29:08.839 --> 00:29:10.133
What?

418
00:29:24.511 --> 00:29:26.261
David. this is an opportunity.

419
00:29:26.262 --> 00:29:29.201
Not just to repay your
debt. but to be a hero.

420
00:29:29.202 --> 00:29:30.445
To be a soldier.

421
00:29:30.446 --> 00:29:32.890
To fight for something greater than us.

422
00:29:37.431 --> 00:29:38.753
See you tonight.

423
00:29:54.528 --> 00:29:58.200
Listen. a scouser goes to a prostitute

424
00:29:58.325 --> 00:30:01.777
and she says to him. "Do
you fancy a blow job?"

425
00:30:01.932 --> 00:30:04.284
He says. "I don't know. Will
it affect me dole money?"

426
00:30:06.858 --> 00:30:11.618
So Paddy. right. Paddy
gets arrested for rape.

427
00:30:11.789 --> 00:30:14.240
And they put him in a line
up with ten other blokes

428
00:30:14.241 --> 00:30:16.362
and they escort this woman in.

429
00:30:16.363 --> 00:30:20.437
and Paddy yells out. "That's
her! I'd recognise her anywhere!"

430
00:30:23.885 --> 00:30:26.111
Listen. two monkeys in a bath...

431
00:30:26.112 --> 00:30:27.583
So what have you got?

432
00:30:28.891 --> 00:30:31.443
So I ask around the immigrant clubs.

433
00:30:31.627 --> 00:30:35.244
I hate those places. full of foreigners.

434
00:30:35.900 --> 00:30:38.727
I speak to Sergei. He's the caretaker.

435
00:30:38.728 --> 00:30:41.984
"Sergei. what do you
know about a Moscow hood.

436
00:30:41.985 --> 00:30:45.253
ruthless bastard. peels apples?"

437
00:30:45.266 --> 00:30:47.631
And he goes pale

438
00:30:47.632 --> 00:30:50.581
and he says. "You mean Odin?"

439
00:30:50.924 --> 00:30:53.028
- Odin?
- Mmm.

440
00:30:53.029 --> 00:30:56.674
Anyway. then he get all scared

441
00:30:56.675 --> 00:30:59.080
and he says. "Shut up.

442
00:30:59.081 --> 00:31:03.152
What do I know about Russian
hoods? Leave me alone."

443
00:31:05.118 --> 00:31:06.603
This is all I get.

444
00:31:07.964 --> 00:31:09.574
But listen to Kitty...

445
00:31:10.555 --> 00:31:13.112
I got a bad feeling about this.

446
00:31:13.485 --> 00:31:16.186
When Sergei talk about this Odin.

447
00:31:17.076 --> 00:31:18.428
he's scared.

448
00:31:19.710 --> 00:31:22.181
I'm saying be careful.

449
00:31:23.830 --> 00:31:26.045
You're too beautiful to die.

450
00:31:35.956 --> 00:31:37.737
Why are you putting the microphone there?

451
00:31:38.264 --> 00:31:40.908
Oh. uh. because it's where we'd stand.

452
00:31:40.909 --> 00:31:42.622
It's the door. window.

453
00:31:44.182 --> 00:31:45.679
Why this flat?

454
00:31:46.526 --> 00:31:48.024
I don't understand.

455
00:31:50.023 --> 00:31:52.471
What's so special about this flat?

456
00:31:52.879 --> 00:31:56.011
Um. do we have a coffin?

457
00:31:56.509 --> 00:31:58.227
To put David in.

458
00:31:58.456 --> 00:32:00.015
When he's shot.

459
00:32:00.498 --> 00:32:02.091
By the KGB.

460
00:32:04.451 --> 00:32:06.244
To put his dead body in?

461
00:32:07.676 --> 00:32:10.163
It's humour to lighten... lighten the mood.

462
00:32:18.876 --> 00:32:20.254
Okay.

463
00:32:20.419 --> 00:32:21.450
You'll be fine.

464
00:32:21.451 --> 00:32:22.744
Stay calm.

465
00:32:22.841 --> 00:32:24.809
Remember. we're just down the corridor.

466
00:32:31.482 --> 00:32:32.971
The man that came to
your flat this morning.

467
00:32:32.972 --> 00:32:36.006
one of them peeled an apple
with a knife. do you remember?

468
00:32:36.370 --> 00:32:37.424
Yeah.

469
00:32:37.425 --> 00:32:39.117
If he is one of the men you let in.

470
00:32:39.390 --> 00:32:40.996
I want you to say.

471
00:32:41.151 --> 00:32:44.363
"I almost bought some vodka. but I
thought it was a bit of a cliché."

472
00:32:44.364 --> 00:32:46.380
Say it over there. by the microphone.

473
00:32:47.188 --> 00:32:47.928
What?

474
00:32:47.929 --> 00:32:49.719
"I almost bought some vodka.

475
00:32:49.861 --> 00:32:52.257
but I thought it was a bit of a cliché."

476
00:32:52.258 --> 00:32:53.618
I...

477
00:32:53.731 --> 00:32:56.646
almost bought some vodka. but I
thought it was a bit of a cliché.

478
00:32:57.473 --> 00:32:58.939
If...

479
00:32:59.320 --> 00:33:01.274
If it's the man who peeled the apple.

480
00:33:01.275 --> 00:33:02.709
Yeah.

481
00:33:54.196 --> 00:33:56.446
Multiple movements in the corridor.

482
00:33:57.499 --> 00:33:58.936
The door is opening.

483
00:33:59.995 --> 00:34:02.372
David has moved to the centre of the room.

484
00:34:02.605 --> 00:34:03.633
two men have entered behind him.

485
00:34:03.634 --> 00:34:05.998
one heavy set.

486
00:34:06.259 --> 00:34:08.097
the other lithe.

487
00:34:08.192 --> 00:34:11.498
there's no sound of the impact
of their shoes on the floor.

488
00:34:12.292 --> 00:34:15.697
just the creak of the boards.
so they're wearing rubber soles.

489
00:34:15.735 --> 00:34:17.770
The heavy one is still
in front of the door.

490
00:34:17.771 --> 00:34:21.572
<i>This is excellent. David.
you've done very well.</i>

491
00:34:21.573 --> 00:34:23.027
I can't hear what they're saying.

492
00:34:23.028 --> 00:34:24.491
<i>Do you...</i>

493
00:34:24.573 --> 00:34:26.722
<i>Do you want something to drink?</i>

494
00:34:26.817 --> 00:34:28.549
<i>I almost. uh...</i>

495
00:34:28.550 --> 00:34:30.651
<i>I almost bought some vodka.</i>

496
00:34:30.652 --> 00:34:32.883
<i>but I thought it was a bit of a cliché.</i>

497
00:34:33.600 --> 00:34:36.284
Now the other one's crossing
quickly to the window.

498
00:34:36.764 --> 00:34:38.228
He's closing the blinds.

499
00:34:38.229 --> 00:34:39.934
Why's he closing the blinds?

500
00:34:41.716 --> 00:34:43.231
What's going on?

501
00:34:44.114 --> 00:34:45.329
What's he saying?

502
00:34:45.330 --> 00:34:46.641
Jesus...

503
00:35:02.835 --> 00:35:04.456
Shit!

504
00:35:38.368 --> 00:35:39.880
Stay here.

505
00:35:39.917 --> 00:35:41.102
All right.

506
00:36:08.605 --> 00:36:10.743
- Do you think he's all right?
- I doubt it.

507
00:36:11.198 --> 00:36:12.908
You just hit him with a plank.

508
00:36:14.451 --> 00:36:15.738
Come on.

509
00:36:16.479 --> 00:36:17.760
It's not him.

510
00:36:18.293 --> 00:36:19.618
It's not who?

511
00:36:20.286 --> 00:36:22.197
Joe? Hey!

512
00:36:28.646 --> 00:36:30.117
You go that way.

513
00:36:31.321 --> 00:36:33.203
Hey. how come you get the gun?

514
00:36:33.658 --> 00:36:35.012
Joe!

515
00:36:47.339 --> 00:36:48.491
Joe!

516
00:37:19.049 --> 00:37:20.302
Hello. Joe.

517
00:37:23.682 --> 00:37:25.450
Drop the gun or I'll shoot.

518
00:37:25.542 --> 00:37:28.694
If you do. the muscles
in my arm will spasm.

519
00:37:28.695 --> 00:37:33.293
I pull the trigger. and your
friend will die very messily.

520
00:37:33.985 --> 00:37:36.087
Let us try to avoid that.

521
00:37:36.786 --> 00:37:39.750
Joe don't shoot. Joe!

522
00:37:39.751 --> 00:37:42.345
If you wanted to shoot him.
you would have done it by now.

523
00:37:45.427 --> 00:37:47.970
You never had any problem
shooting an unarmed woman.

524
00:37:47.971 --> 00:37:49.488
She was a traitor.

525
00:37:49.637 --> 00:37:51.267
Which reminds me.

526
00:37:51.304 --> 00:37:53.205
what do they know about you?

527
00:37:53.206 --> 00:37:54.710
They know everything.

528
00:37:55.467 --> 00:37:56.863
Liar.

529
00:37:57.218 --> 00:38:01.547
Joe. when you imagine this
moment. as I'm sure you have.

530
00:38:01.611 --> 00:38:03.087
what happens?

531
00:38:06.305 --> 00:38:07.725
I kill you.

532
00:38:09.925 --> 00:38:13.453
Then. what are you waiting for?

533
00:38:13.605 --> 00:38:18.145
If he dies. you can say he
was caught in the crossfire.

534
00:38:19.833 --> 00:38:21.593
No one will know.

535
00:38:23.634 --> 00:38:25.205
Come on. Joe.

536
00:38:25.223 --> 00:38:26.596
Joe. please!

537
00:38:28.347 --> 00:38:29.596
Please!

538
00:38:52.396 --> 00:38:53.911
Goodbye. Joe.

539
00:38:54.445 --> 00:38:56.024
This must be hard.

540
00:38:56.539 --> 00:39:00.996
But don't worry. Soon
everything will become clear.

541
00:39:06.004 --> 00:39:07.539
Oh. shit.

542
00:39:10.358 --> 00:39:11.606
No!

543
00:39:12.155 --> 00:39:13.322
Yulia!

544
00:39:14.717 --> 00:39:16.243
Yulia!

545
00:39:16.687 --> 00:39:18.352
Yulia!

546
00:39:26.193 --> 00:39:28.363
No!

547
00:39:58.203 --> 00:39:59.436
Bad show.

548
00:40:22.528 --> 00:40:24.993
The geese fly south in winter.

549
00:40:26.322 --> 00:40:28.361
Ah. yes.

550
00:40:28.362 --> 00:40:30.853
But the gander is. um...

551
00:40:30.854 --> 00:40:33.124
No. The gander tends to...

552
00:40:33.297 --> 00:40:35.330
What? "The gander"?

553
00:40:35.403 --> 00:40:38.676
And their eggs are most

554
00:40:38.677 --> 00:40:41.561
- plentiful when the...
- Please stop.

555
00:40:41.562 --> 00:40:43.298
This is painful.

556
00:40:45.237 --> 00:40:47.308
I heard what happened.

557
00:40:48.002 --> 00:40:49.707
Oh. my love.

558
00:40:49.838 --> 00:40:50.932
I'm fine.

559
00:40:50.933 --> 00:40:53.709
Joe and that Jim chap engaged.

560
00:40:54.790 --> 00:40:56.661
I'm ashamed to say I hid.

561
00:40:56.662 --> 00:40:58.684
I'd have been furious if you hadn't.

562
00:41:00.323 --> 00:41:03.728
I want to have the conversation.

563
00:41:04.663 --> 00:41:05.983
- Oh. Sarah.
- No. not that one.

564
00:41:05.984 --> 00:41:07.592
The Marconi one.

565
00:41:08.994 --> 00:41:11.124
Someone died tonight.

566
00:41:11.716 --> 00:41:13.350
Yards away from you.

567
00:41:13.351 --> 00:41:14.817
All I'm saying is. with
your skills you could walk...

568
00:41:14.818 --> 00:41:17.579
... straight into somewhere like Marconi.

569
00:41:20.307 --> 00:41:22.619
Is this really about my safety?

570
00:41:22.620 --> 00:41:24.720
You're destined for great things.

571
00:41:25.218 --> 00:41:28.746
and a husband who tinkers with
wires and microphones is hardly...

572
00:41:28.747 --> 00:41:31.662
Is that why you think I want
you to get a different job?

573
00:41:33.975 --> 00:41:37.247
To make you more suitable for me?

574
00:41:38.893 --> 00:41:40.548
People talk. Sarah.

575
00:41:40.549 --> 00:41:43.184
Because they don't understand us.

576
00:41:45.249 --> 00:41:46.813
Not in this world.

577
00:41:59.975 --> 00:42:01.306
Come on.

578
00:42:05.654 --> 00:42:06.943
Best case scenario.

579
00:42:06.944 --> 00:42:09.135
Moscow don't know Arkady has turned.

580
00:42:09.136 --> 00:42:11.280
They think David approached us directly.

581
00:42:11.281 --> 00:42:13.035
and that's why they killed him.

582
00:42:13.951 --> 00:42:17.244
From Joe's report. he clearly didn't
want to be part of any operation.

583
00:42:17.625 --> 00:42:20.630
ours or theirs. so it's
not hard to imagine.

584
00:42:21.935 --> 00:42:25.016
I want Arkady taken
into protective custody.

585
00:42:25.242 --> 00:42:26.867
He can be debriefed later.

586
00:42:26.868 --> 00:42:28.157
just get him out of harm's way.

587
00:42:28.158 --> 00:42:29.615
Wait.

588
00:42:29.655 --> 00:42:31.237
Let's think about this.

589
00:42:33.074 --> 00:42:37.298
Moscow will know Arkady won't
have used his real name with David.

590
00:42:37.299 --> 00:42:38.553
any more than we would.

591
00:42:38.554 --> 00:42:41.017
You think Moscow might
keep Arkady as a go-between?

592
00:42:41.018 --> 00:42:43.547
If this operation is as top
secret as we've been told.

593
00:42:43.548 --> 00:42:46.057
they won't want to risk
bringing more people in.

594
00:42:46.058 --> 00:42:50.035
We just won't know for sure until
they contact Arkady with the next name.

595
00:42:50.036 --> 00:42:52.618
Or his body is washed up on a beach.

596
00:43:04.728 --> 00:43:09.146
There is another possible explanation
as to why they killed David.

597
00:43:12.076 --> 00:43:13.776
We have a mole.

598
00:43:14.686 --> 00:43:17.202
Not just in MI5. but in this group.

599
00:43:17.203 --> 00:43:18.723
In this room.

600
00:43:18.781 --> 00:43:23.531
Joe. Daddy. Bobby. Alan.
Wendy. Jim or myself.

601
00:43:23.532 --> 00:43:25.961
One of us told Moscow about this.

602
00:43:46.971 --> 00:43:51.239
The signal has been given. Another name has
been left for Arkady in the dead-letter drop.

603
00:43:51.682 --> 00:43:53.618
If Moscow know he's working for us.

604
00:43:53.619 --> 00:43:55.811
It'll be a trap. They'll
be waiting for him.

605
00:43:55.812 --> 00:43:57.990
I say. get Arkady into a safe house.

606
00:43:57.991 --> 00:43:59.218
wait for Moscow's next move.

607
00:43:59.219 --> 00:44:02.443
Except Moscow's next move could be
the Red Army marching down the mount.

608
00:44:02.444 --> 00:44:04.820
Daddy. we need a decision.

609
00:44:08.837 --> 00:44:09.962
We continue.

610
00:44:09.963 --> 00:44:13.116
We assume Moscow don't know about Arkady.

611
00:44:13.694 --> 00:44:16.456
We assume there is no mole.

612
00:44:17.515 --> 00:44:20.774
We let Arkady collect the next name.

613
00:44:21.561 --> 00:44:23.400
We endanger the few

614
00:44:23.863 --> 00:44:26.424
to protect the many.

615
00:44:43.905 --> 00:44:45.119
Come.

616
00:44:55.222 --> 00:44:56.892
The agent that was killed in Poland.

617
00:44:56.893 --> 00:44:59.742
I had allowed our relationship to become...

618
00:45:01.844 --> 00:45:03.536
... unprofessional.

619
00:45:03.841 --> 00:45:07.042
She was killed by the same man
that David Hexton met at the flat.

620
00:45:09.210 --> 00:45:11.313
David was

621
00:45:11.314 --> 00:45:12.937
scared.

622
00:45:12.938 --> 00:45:14.529
unreliable

623
00:45:16.434 --> 00:45:18.072
and vulnerable.

624
00:45:21.488 --> 00:45:23.739
In my eagerness to expose this man.

625
00:45:24.875 --> 00:45:29.199
I convinced him to participate
in the operation that killed him.

626
00:45:30.059 --> 00:45:33.487
If I reassign you. will you
abandon your search for this man?

627
00:45:34.267 --> 00:45:36.951
- No.
- Then our objectives are the same.

628
00:45:37.069 --> 00:45:38.460
Find him

629
00:45:38.791 --> 00:45:42.047
and you find the truth of Operation Glass.

630
00:45:42.909 --> 00:45:44.628
You know what I was doing in Poland?

631
00:45:44.629 --> 00:45:49.374
Yes. You were attempting to
infiltrate the Soviet Security Service.

632
00:45:49.375 --> 00:45:53.293
Your cover was that of a
disaffected MI5 officer.

633
00:45:53.294 --> 00:45:54.949
Once you had gained their trust.

634
00:45:54.950 --> 00:45:57.874
the plan was to relay intel back to us

635
00:45:57.875 --> 00:45:59.749
and feed them prepared

636
00:46:00.458 --> 00:46:02.300
misinformation.

637
00:46:03.467 --> 00:46:04.950
But that's not true.

638
00:46:06.951 --> 00:46:08.264
Really?

639
00:46:10.914 --> 00:46:13.179
That's what it says in your file.

640
00:46:13.998 --> 00:46:15.565
I should know.

641
00:46:15.781 --> 00:46:17.290
I wrote it.

642
00:46:18.183 --> 00:46:20.228
Why? Hmm?

643
00:46:21.758 --> 00:46:23.285
Why save me?

644
00:46:25.060 --> 00:46:29.150
It's not quite as
altruistic as it might seem.

645
00:46:29.613 --> 00:46:32.702
This second chance I've given
you will pass unremarked.

646
00:46:32.703 --> 00:46:34.417
we are Englishmen after all.

647
00:46:34.418 --> 00:46:35.987
But I know

648
00:46:36.462 --> 00:46:39.212
it will not be forgotten.

649
00:46:40.738 --> 00:46:44.281
Could I rely on you
never to betray a country?

650
00:46:45.203 --> 00:46:46.675
Perhaps not.

651
00:46:46.975 --> 00:46:50.689
Could I rely on you never to betray me?

652
00:46:51.595 --> 00:46:53.202
Yes.

653
00:46:53.487 --> 00:46:55.228
I believe I could.

654
00:46:55.587 --> 00:46:57.156
I'm sorry. Joe.

655
00:46:57.927 --> 00:46:59.955
I have to trust someone.

656
00:47:00.427 --> 00:47:02.217
and I've decided

657
00:47:02.622 --> 00:47:04.108
it's you.

658
00:47:26.285 --> 00:47:27.683
I understand now.

659
00:47:32.052 --> 00:47:34.113
After I saw what they did to David.

660
00:47:37.373 --> 00:47:39.859
I mean. I still don't
think there's anything

661
00:47:39.979 --> 00:47:41.989
impressive or

662
00:47:42.331 --> 00:47:44.266
romantic about this.

663
00:47:44.267 --> 00:47:46.543
But I now see you're necessary.

664
00:47:49.260 --> 00:47:51.542
If the mission is all that this is about.

665
00:47:51.862 --> 00:47:53.469
Who was the girl?

666
00:47:58.700 --> 00:47:59.990
I forget.

667
00:48:06.780 --> 00:48:10.182
This is an opportunity for you
to be a soldier. To be a hero.

668
00:48:10.556 --> 00:48:12.709
To fight for something greater than us.

669
00:48:15.032 --> 00:48:16.688
Would I be safe?

670
00:48:20.099 --> 00:48:21.567
Trust me.

671
00:48:46.991 --> 00:48:48.177
Kitty?

672
00:49:00.345 --> 00:49:01.519
Kitty?

673
00:49:08.113 --> 00:49:09.218
Kitty?

674
00:49:32.397 --> 00:49:34.020
Kitty?

675
00:49:56.966 --> 00:49:58.278
Kitty!

676
00:49:58.358 --> 00:49:59.748
Oh. my God!

677
00:50:03.175 --> 00:50:05.266
Don't speak. Don't speak.

678
00:50:06.953 --> 00:50:09.705
I'll get help... Okay.

679
00:50:10.330 --> 00:50:15.100
Why you do this to me. beautiful?

680
00:50:15.222 --> 00:50:16.519
What?

681
00:50:17.328 --> 00:50:19.638
They said

682
00:50:21.306 --> 00:50:24.540
you ordered it.

683
00:50:24.570 --> 00:50:25.928
What are you saying?

684
00:50:26.188 --> 00:50:28.498
You lied to me. Joe.

685
00:50:30.000 --> 00:50:33.150
You're a traitor.

686
00:50:44.203 --> 00:50:46.963
Yulia! Yulia!

687
00:50:47.446 --> 00:50:49.355
Yulia!

688
00:50:49.510 --> 00:50:50.758
No!

689
00:50:52.286 --> 00:50:54.001
Yulia!

690
00:50:55.077 --> 00:50:56.578
No!

691
00:51:06.118 --> 00:51:07.572
I'm so sorry.

692
00:51:20.440 --> 00:51:24.130
